column1: #Text=Alipurduar is located in the north-east corner of West Bengal , bordering on Bhutan and Assam .
#Text=The area is in eastern Dooars , Himalayan foothills , with thick forests and a variety of wildlife .
#Text=The entire region exudes great scenic beauty .

#Text=Alipurduar Junction railway station is on the New Jalpaiguri-Alipurduar-Samuktala Road line ( originally metre gauge but later converted to broad gauge ) and New Alipurduar railway station is on the New Jalpaiguri-Guwahati main line ( broad gauge ) with a variety of options for trains from all over India .
#Text=Alipurduar is on National Highway 31D , with links to NH 31 and NH 31C .
#Text=This means easy access to the rest of North Bengal and the North-east .
#Text=Large number of buses ply on these routes .
#Text=Buxa Tiger Reserve ( Located in Buxa National Park - marked on the map ) .
#Text=Buxa Tiger Reserve is located near Alipurduar in the eastern Dooars .
#Text=Amongst wildlife in the tiger reserve are tiger , leopard ( black panther also ) , elephant , clouded leopard , Himalayan black bear , barking deer , gaur , pangolin , and python .
#Text=Buxa Fort , Buxaduar , Rajabhatkhawa Gram Panchayet , Kalchini block ( The Motorable Road ended at Santrabari Range Office of Buxa Tiger Reserve .
#Text=From Santrabari one have to trek 4.9 km ( 1 hour ) via Sadar Bazar . ) , ✉ ecoman.tamal@gmail.com .
#Text=Buxa Fort was conquered after the Dooars Bhutan war in 1865 .
#Text=The fort was primarily used as a military barracks , to protect the Indo-Bhutan border .
#Text=Later used as detainment camp ( 1931-1939 & 1942 -1947 ) for Indian Freedom Fighters .
#Text=The 2 km fort is the symbol of Indian Freedom Movement .
#Text=It has a railway station on the New Jalpaiguri-Alipurduar-Samuktala line and is also connected by road .
#Text=Nature Interpretation Centre and Tiger Rescue Centre are points of interest at Rajabhatkhawa .
#Text=Exotic scenic beauty at the foot of the Bhutan Hills , Rich variety of wild life .
#Text=Rasik Beel ( South of Kamakhyaguri , about 34 km from Alipurduar ) .

#Text=Rasik Beel is a wet land complex ( in Bengali , beel means large water body ) and bird sanctuary , with such birds as lesser whistling teal , common teal , cotton teal , dapchick , bronze winged jacana , pheasant-tailed janacana , shoveler , barheaded goose , white-eyed poacherd etc.
#Text=A 70 feet high watch tower has been constructed by Coochbehar Forest Division .
#Text=There is a mini zoo at Rasik Beel , with tortoise , gharial , leopard , spotted deer , peafowl and other inmates .
#Text=Hotel Dooars Mountain , Buxa Feeder Road , Shanti Nagar , ☏ +913564251491 .
#Text=Hotel Shivam , Samuktala Road ( Near M.N.Bus Terminus ) , ☏ +913564257720 .
#Text=It is a 16 beds dormitory , at an altitude of 2600 ft , run by local Eco Development Committee for Buxa Duar .
